# Database Conventions

Extracted from the actual Supabase schema. Follow these when creating or modifying tables.

**Applies in both plan mode and agent mode.** Reference these conventions when proposing schema and when executing migrations.

## Table Naming

| Pattern | Purpose | Examples |
|---|---|---|
| `<domain>_master` | Primary entity definition | `reward_master`, `tier_master`, `campaign_master`, `workflow_master`, `persona_master` |
| `<domain>` (no suffix) | Simpler primary entities | `mission`, `checkin`, `codes`, `multiplier` |
| `<domain>_ledger` | Immutable transaction/event log | `wallet_ledger`, `purchase_ledger`, `checkin_ledger`, `tier_change_ledger`, `referral_ledger` |
| `<domain>_log_<type>` | Alternative log pattern | `mission_log_completion`, `mission_log_outcome_distribution` |
| `<domain>_conditions` | Rules/criteria attached to entity | `mission_conditions`, `tier_conditions`, `earn_conditions`, `checkin_conditions`, `reward_points_conditions` |
| `<domain>_progress` | User progress/tracking | `mission_progress`, `tier_progress`, `tier_progression_metrics` |
| `<domain>_config` | Configuration | `activity_currency_config`, `feature_config`, `admin_menu_config` |
| `user_<entity>` | Per-user records | `user_wallet`, `user_tags`, `user_benefit`, `user_sessions`, `user_accounts` |
| `cs_<entity>` | CS module tables | `cs_conversations`, `cs_messages`, `cs_brand_config` |
| `<domain>_import_jobs` | Bulk import tracking | `codes_import_jobs`, `card_import_batches`, `bulk_import_batches` |
| `<domain>_staging` | Temporary staging data | `codes_staging`, `reward_promo_code_staging` |

**Shared tables** (used by both loyalty and CS): `workflow_master`, `workflow_node`, `workflow_edge`, `workflow_trigger`, `workflow_log` — use `domain` column ('loyalty' or 'cs') to filter.

## Standard Columns — Every Table

| Column | Type | Default | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `id` | `uuid` | `gen_random_uuid()` | Always PK. Never bigint for new tables. |
| `merchant_id` | `uuid NOT NULL` | — | Every multi-tenant table. FK to `merchant_master`. Used in RLS. |
| `created_at` | `timestamptz` | `now()` | Always present. |
| `updated_at` | `timestamptz` | `now()` | On master/config tables. Maintained by `trigger_set_updated_at`. |

## Standard Columns — By Purpose

### Identity & Naming
| Column | Type | When to use |
|---|---|---|
| `<entity>_code` | `text` | Human-readable identifier (mission_code, store_code, reward_code, workflow_code). Distinct from uuid `id`. |
| `<entity>_name` | `text` | Display name when prefixed (mission_name, tier_name, persona_name, store_name). |
| `name` | `text` | Display name for simpler tables (reward_master, workflow_master, form_templates). |
| `description` | `text` | Single description. Use `description_<variant>` when multiple needed (description_headline, description_body, description_tc). |

### Status & Flags
| Column | Type | Default | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `is_active` | `boolean` | `true` | **Standard for new tables.** On/off toggle. Legacy tables may use `active_status` — do not rename, but use `is_active` for all new work. |
| `is_<state>` | `boolean` | varies | State flags: `is_claimed`, `is_milestone`, `is_featured`, `is_custom_answer`. Always `is_` prefix. |
| `has_<feature>` | `boolean` | `false` | Feature presence: `has_time_conditions`. |
| `status` | `enum` | varies | When lifecycle states are needed (form_status, purchase_status). Use PostgreSQL enum types. |

### Time Windows
| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `window_start` | `timestamptz` | Eligibility/availability start. Pair with `window_end`. |
| `window_end` | `timestamptz` | Eligibility/availability end. |
| `window_start_time` / `window_end_time` | `time` | Time-of-day restrictions (without date). |
| `<action>_at` | `timestamptz` | Action timestamps: `claimed_at`, `activated_at`, `completed_at`, `performed_at`, `expired_at`. |

### Foreign Keys & References
| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `<entity>_id` | `uuid` | FK to another table (user_id, mission_id, tier_id, store_id, reward_id). |
| `source_type` + `source_id` | `text` + `uuid` | Polymorphic reference — what triggered this record. |
| `external_ref` | `text` | Reference to external system. |
| `dedup_key` | `text` | Idempotency key to prevent duplicate processing. |

### Arrays (Filter Lists)
| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `allowed_<entity>` | `uuid[]` | Eligibility filter arrays: `allowed_tier`, `allowed_persona`, `allowed_tags`. |
| `<entity>_ids` | `uuid[]` | Multi-select references: `product_ids`, `sku_ids`, `category_ids`, `brand_ids`, `tier_ids`, `tag_ids`. |

### Amounts & Metrics
| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `amount` | `numeric` | Monetary or point amounts. Never `float`. |
| `<prefix>_amount` | `numeric` | Qualified amounts: `total_amount`, `final_amount`, `discount_amount`, `outcome_amount`. |
| `balance_before` / `balance_after` | `integer` | Ledger balance snapshots. |
| `points_required` | `numeric` | Cost in points. |

### Flexible Data
| Column | Type | Default | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `metadata` | `jsonb` | `'{}'` | Generic extensible data. |
| `config` | `jsonb` | `'{}'` | Structured configuration. |
| `field_definitions` | `jsonb` | `'{}'` | Dynamic schema definitions. |
| `images` | `text[]` or `jsonb` | — | Image URLs. Prefer `text[]` for simple lists, `jsonb` for structured. |

## Data Type Rules

- **IDs**: `uuid` with `gen_random_uuid()`. Never serial/bigint for new tables.
- **Timestamps**: Always `timestamptz`. Never `timestamp without time zone`.
- **Money/points**: `numeric`. Never `float` or `real`.
- **Counts**: `integer`.
- **Text**: `text`. Avoid `varchar` unless there's a real length constraint.
- **Booleans**: `boolean` with meaningful default.
- **Enums**: PostgreSQL `CREATE TYPE` enums for fixed status values.
- **Arrays**: `uuid[]` or `text[]` for typed lists.
- **Flexible**: `jsonb` with `'{}'::jsonb` default.

## RLS Pattern

Every multi-tenant table:
```sql
ALTER TABLE <table> ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
CREATE POLICY "merchant_isolation" ON <table>
  FOR ALL USING (merchant_id = get_current_merchant_id());
```

## Trigger Pattern

Master/config tables get an `updated_at` trigger:
```sql
CREATE TRIGGER set_updated_at BEFORE UPDATE ON <table>
  FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION trigger_set_updated_at();
```
